  <description type="morphology">Stems 2–5 mm.  Leaves 1–2.5 mm, distal laminal cells mostly isodiametric, 1:1, with a few cells 2:1 or transversely elongate, areolation somewhat irregular, proximal cells longer.  Seta 0.5–2 mm, flexuose when dry.  Capsule spherical to short-ovate, 0.4–0.6 mm.  Peristome absent.  Spores 6–10 µm.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Moist, acidic boulders; montane, predominantly alpine;</description>
