  <discussion>The spherical or short-ovate capsules absent peristome teeth and the somewhat shorter distal laminal cells distinguish Brachydontium olympicum from B. trichodes.  This is a circum-North Pacific montane species, which should be sought for in coastal areas of Siberia.</discussion>
